6) Create a Java program that defines a final variable in a parent class and accesses it through inheritance. Show that it cannot be changed by the subclass.
-->6) Final variable in parent class accessed through inheritance
class Parent {
    final int x = 100;
}

class Child extends Parent {

    void display() {
        System.out.println("Value of x = " + x);

        // x = 200; // Compile-time Error
    }
}

public class InheritanceFinalDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Child c = new Child();
        c.display();
    }
}
Output
Value of x = 100
Key Point

The child class can access the final variable inherited from the parent class, but it cannot modify it because final variables can be assigned only once.
